#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-hppa-medium.xml:65
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Gentoo Linux can be installed using one of three <e>stage</e> tarball files. A\n"
"stage file is a tarball (compressed archive) that contains a minimal\n"
"environment.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><ul><li>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-hppa-medium.xml:72
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    A stage1 file contains nothing more than a compiler, Portage (Gentoo's\n"
"    software management system) and a couple of packages on which the \n"
"    compiler or Portage depends. \n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><ul><li>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-hppa-medium.xml:77
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    A stage2 file contains a so-called bootstrapped system, a minimal\n"
"    environment from which one can start building all other necessary \n"
"    applications that make a Gentoo environment complete.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><ul><li>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-hppa-medium.xml:82
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    A stage3 file contains a prebuilt minimal system which is almost fully\n"
"    deployable. It only lacks a few applications where you, the Gentoo user, \n"
"    needs to choose which one you want to install.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-hppa-medium.xml:89
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"We will opt for a stage3 installation throughout this document. If you want to\n"
"perform a Gentoo installation using the stage1 or stage2 files, please use the\n"
"installation instructions in the <uri\n"
"link=\"/doc/en/handbook/handbook-hppa.xml\">Gentoo Handbook</uri>. They do\n"
"require a working Internet connection though.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-hppa-medium.xml:99
#, no-wrap
msgid "Gentoo Universal Installation CD"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-hppa-medium.xml:103
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"An Installation CD is a bootable medium which contains a self-sustained Gentoo \n"
"environment. It allows you to boot Linux from the CD. During the boot process \n"
"your hardware is detected and the appropriate drivers are loaded. The Gentoo \n"
"Installation CDs are maintained by Gentoo developers.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-hppa-medium.xml:110
#, no-wrap
msgid "There currently are two Installation CDs available:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><ul><li>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-hppa-medium.xml:115
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    The Universal Installation CD contains everything you need to install \n"
"    Gentoo. It provides stage3 files for common architectures, source code \n"
"    for the extra applications you need to choose from and, of course, the \n"
"    installation instructions for your architecture.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><ul><li>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-hppa-medium.xml:121
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    The Minimal Installation CD contains only a minimal environment that allows \n"
"    you to boot up and configure your network so you can connect to the \n"
"    Internet. It does not contain any additional files and cannot be used \n"
"    during the current installation approach.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-hppa-medium.xml:129
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Gentoo also provides a Package CD. This is no Installation CD but an additional \n"
"resource that you can exploit during the installation of your Gentoo system. It\n"
"contains prebuilt packages (the so-called GRP set) that allows you to easily \n"
"and quickly install additional applications (such as OpenOffice.org, KDE, \n"
"GNOME, ...) immediately after the Gentoo installation and right before you \n"
"update your Portage tree.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-hppa-medium.xml:138
#, no-wrap
msgid "The use of the Package CD is covered later in this document. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><title>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-hppa-medium.xml:146
#, no-wrap
msgid "Download, Burn and Boot the Gentoo Universal Installation CD"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-hppa-medium.xml:148
#, no-wrap
msgid "Downloading and Burning the Installation CD"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-hppa-medium.xml:152
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"You can download the Universal Installation CD (and, if you want to, the \n"
"Packages CD as well) from one of our <uri \n"
"link=\"/main/en/mirrors.xml\">mirrors</uri>. The Installation CD is located in \n"
"the <path>releases/hppa/2005.0/installcd</path> directory;\n"
"the Package CD is located in the <path>releases/hppa/2005.0/packagecd</path>\n"
"directory.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-hppa-medium.xml:161
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Inside those directories you'll find so-called ISO-files. Those are full CD \n"
"images which you can write on a CD-R.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-hppa-medium.xml:166
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"After downloading the file, you can verify its integrity to see if it is \n"
"corrupted or not:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><ul><li>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-hppa-medium.xml:172
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    You can check its MD5 checksum and compare it with the MD5 checksum we \n"
"    provide (for instance with the <c>md5sum</c> tool under Linux/Unix or \n"
"    <uri link=\"http://www.etree.org/md5com.html\">md5sum</uri> for Windows)\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><ul><li>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-hppa-medium.xml:177
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    You can verify the cryptographic signature that we provide. You need to\n"
"    obtain the public key we use (17072058) before you proceed though.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-hppa-medium.xml:183
#, no-wrap
msgid "To fetch our public key using the GnuPG application, run the following command:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-hppa-medium.xml:186
#, no-wrap
msgid "Obtaining the public key"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-hppa-medium.xml:187
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ <i>gpg --keyserver pgp.mit.edu --recv-keys 17072058</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-hppa-medium.xml:191
#, no-wrap
msgid "Now verify the signature:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-hppa-medium.xml:194
#, no-wrap
msgid "Verify the cryptographic signature"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-hppa-medium.xml:195
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ <i>gpg --verify &lt;signature file&gt; &lt;downloaded iso&gt;</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-hppa-medium.xml:199
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"To burn the downloaded ISO(s), you have to select raw-burning. How you\n"
"do this is highly program-dependent. We will discuss <c>cdrecord</c> and\n"
"<c>K3B</c> here; more information can be found in our <uri\n"
"link=\"/doc/en/faq.xml#isoburning\">Gentoo FAQ</uri>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><ul><li>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-hppa-medium.xml:207
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    With cdrecord, you simply type <c>cdrecord dev=/dev/hdc &lt;downloaded iso\n"
"    file&gt;</c> (replace <path>/dev/hdc</path> with your CD-RW drive's device\n"
"    path).\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><ul><li>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-hppa-medium.xml:212
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    With K3B, select <c>Tools</c> &gt; <c>CD</c> &gt; <c>Burn Image</c>. Then\n"
"    you can locate your ISO file within the 'Image to Burn' area. Finally click\n"
"    <c>Start</c>.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-hppa-medium.xml:221
#, no-wrap
msgid "Booting the Universal Installation CD"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><note>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-hppa-medium.xml:225
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you have problems booting the Installation CD or any other media, please \n"
"read the <uri \n"
"link=\"http://www.tldp.org/HOWTO/PA-RISC-Linux-Boot-HOWTO/index.html\">\n"
"PA-RISC Linux Boot HOWTO</uri>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-hppa-medium.xml:232
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Boot your HPPA system. During the boot process, you will see a message similar\n"
"to the following:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-hppa-medium.xml:236
#, no-wrap
msgid "HPPA boot message"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-hppa-medium.xml:237
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Searching for Potential Boot Devices.\n"
"To terminate search, press and hold the ESCAPE key.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-hppa-medium.xml:242
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"When this message appears, press and hold the Esc-key until an option menu\n"
"appears. This can take a while, be patient. By default, you should enter the\n"
"BOOT_ADMIN console. If you receive an option menu, choose <c>Enter Boot\n"
"Administration mode</c> to enter the BOOT_ADMIN console. You should now have an\n"
"'&gt;' prompt.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-hppa-medium.xml:250
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Put the Gentoo Installation CD in the CD-ROM. If you do not know the SCSI ID of \n"
"your CD-ROM drive, your PA-RISC station will search for it when you issue the \n"
"<c>search</c> command.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-hppa-medium.xml:255
#, no-wrap
msgid "Searching for SCSI ID"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-hppa-medium.xml:256
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"&gt; <i>search</i>\n"
"Searching for Devices with Bootable Media.\n"
"To terminate search, please press and hold the ESCAPE key.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-hppa-medium.xml:262
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Your PA-RISC station will now display all the available boot media. This is an\n"
"example result of this command:\n"
